Explicit Check for None:

The code now explicitly checks whether response is None. This ensures that None is treated differently from an actual HTTP response that may have a status code of 500 or higher.
If the response is None, it logs an error and retries as appropriate.
Handling Status Codes >= 500:

If the response is not None but has a status code of 500 or higher, the code will log a warning and retry. This addresses the issue where the system was not retrying when it encountered server errors.
